did.langmaterial: Multiple languages contained in written material specific to country/region. Predominately written in English.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Reccords are primarily arranged by Program.
Some subgroups may contain portions of the material that are arranged by the Rockefeller Foundation traditional series (country code) and subseries (program letter) structure.
Records are arranged as received. Within folders, materials are primarily arranged in reverse chronological order.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Project files transferred to the RAC by Rockefeller Foundation, 1983-1987.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use note
userestrict.p: Rockefeller Foundation has title, copyright, and literary rights in the collection, in so far as it holds them. Rockefeller Archive Center has authority to grant permission to cite and publish archival material from the collection.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Records more than 10 years old are open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC. Researchers interested in accessing digital media (floppy disks, CDs, DVDs, etc.) or audiovisual material (audio cassettes, VHS, etc.) in this collection must use an access surrogate. The original items may not be accessed because of preservation concerns. To request an access surrogate be made, or if you are unsure if there is an access surrogate, please contact an archivist.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Types of records include: project and fellowship material.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: General background on university development in Brazil: i.e. diaries of team visits; overall prospects of RF support; evaluations of progress; Velasquez correspondence (to and from New York) on EFD planning; correspondence with university officials about team visits and RF funding; correspondence and memoranda about overall planning, development and administration of PROPED (program of research and education for development) ; official letters of request and RF notification of allocations for PROPED support.

Agricultural Sciences (A 84) — Correspondence and memoranda about AS interests in EFD program; input on development of agronomy faculty at Cruz das Almas. Correspondence to and from Jim Maner, Susan Almy (rural development), Kenneth Buhr and Eugenio Martiner. Diaries of JA Pino visits.

Health Sciences (A 84) — Correspondence about development of rural and community health projects and Center for the Study of Regional Diseases. Correspondence to and from Willoughby Lathem, Stephen Plank, James Olson. Lathem periodic reports. VC Scott and GS Hayes (NY officers) diaries of visits.

Social Sciences (A 84) — Correspondence and memoranda about the development of a graduate training program of economics and socio-anthropological studies; correspondence and memos and diaries from A Musalem and Fuenzilidia. Diaries of S Almy. Correspondence and reports on micro economic studies and small business enterprise.

Administration (A 84) — Correspondence and memoranda on local office administration and administrative matters concerning operations of EFD program center: i.e. routine correspondence about team visits; budget matters; office and vehicle matters; routine personnel matters; fellowship award administration.
Administration Housing (A 84) — Correspondence, memoranda concerning the purchase or rental of housing for staff assigned to Brazil EFD, including correspondence re utilities and furnishings.
Agreement (NY) — Correspondence, memoranda and agreements re RF participation in an EFD program in Brazil; privileges extended RF staff by Brazilian government.
Program Review (A 82) — Program reviews (1974, 1979) by RF officers and 1979 reviews by outside evaluators Sheldon M. Wolff, Arnold C. Harberger and Eduardo L. Venezian.
Staff Minutes (A 84) — Minutes of meetings held by RF Bahia staff, August 14, 1974 through November 9, 1977

scopecontent.p: (overall Program & Policy)
- General background on university development in Indonesia
- Diaries of RF officers visiting GMU
- Correspondence re RF policy on visiting faculty and personnel assigned to GMU
- Correspondence from A.J. Nyberg re development at GMU
- Correspondence re external assistance (non RF) to GMU
- Correspondence re overall faculty development at GMU; overall library development; overall evaluations of allocations; personnel assigned to GMU
- Program review documents
- News clippings re social, economic and political developments in Indonesia
- Program and policy issues at GMU which involve RF role and funding
- Monthly reports of activities from RF representative, JE Black, 1981-83
- Final report "EFD - cooperative program, GMU and RF, 1971-83
Administration

- Correspondence and memoranda on administrative matters concerning the operation of the EFD program center office, i.e. routine correspondence about officer and team visits (itineraries, travel arrangements, appointments) - to and from RF representative, A.J. Nyberg, and acting representative, R. Northrup
- Correspondence and notification about bank deposits; audits; budgets and accountings: charges to local EFD center budget (see Note 1 below)
- Personnel policies for local staff
- Correspondence about starting at English speaking school in Yogykarta
- Correspondence with field staff concerning articles and books which are of interest to them
- Correspondence about the purchase of books and journals for RF staff members
Note: 1) Correspondence and memoranda related to and charged to items shown in EFD center budget (attached) should be filed in 652 UD - Administration, with the exception of cars and housing.
2) Correspondence re housing: SEE 652 UD - Gadjah Mada University - Staff Housing
3) Correspondence re autos: SEE 652 UD - Administration - Automobiles
Administration Automobiles
- Correspondence, memoranda concerning purchase and shipment of vehicles for RF staff assigned to GMU
Agreement
- Correspondence, memoranda concerning RF agreement with Government of the Republic of Indonesia
Agricultural Sciences
- Correspondence and memoranda about AS interests at GMU; with AS field staff assigned to GMU. Correspondence dealing with the establishment and maintenance of relationships with agro complex at GMU
- General correspondence about RF agricultural sciences fellows from GMU
- Diaries of RF staff assigned to GMU (Tillman and Thompson, Crowder and Warwick)
- Reports and papers on AS subjects in relation to curriculum development
- Occasional "situation" reports vis a vis agro complex at GMU
- Report by Tillman (December 1980) of seven year experience in EFD at GMU
Medical Sciences (or Health Sciences)
- Correspondence, memoranda and diaries of Lucien Gregg and Joe Wray concerning possibilities for an RF role in medicine and health related areas at GMU
- Correspondence re development of a medical team at GMU
- Reports of consultants assigned to investigate medical and health departments and facilities at GMU
- Correspondence and memoranda to and from Jon Rohde and Robert Northrup on medical and health related issues, programs and policies
- Sundry mimeographed project studies on comprehensive community health, population studies, child health
Social Sciences
- Diaries of K.W. Thompson and social science officers concerning an SS role at GMU
- Correspondence and memoranda to and from D. Hedley and C. MacAndrews on general social science related issues, programs and policies
- Because of A.J. Nyberg's role as RF representative and economics professor at GMU, 652 UD and 652 UD - Administration should also be consulted for possible social science related correspondence
- Diaries of D. Hedley and C. MacAndrews
Allocations and Fellows
Individual files are maintained for each allocation (see 652 UD - Minutes for mark up) and for each Indonesian fellow (652 E)
